# ============================================================
# ENTITY DETAIL OPERATIONS
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: operations
domain: detail
subdomain: entity-detail
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

purpose:
Defines operational handling for entity detail.

scope:
Covers entity detail publication, revision,
snapshot inspection, visibility incidents,
and archival review.

required_behavior:
- Support entity-detail publication and revision.
- Support visibility-safe operational review.
- Support historical entity-detail inspection.
- Support snapshot chain verification.
- Support containment on profile visibility incidents.

state_model:
entity_detail_operational_state:
- prepared
- reviewed
- active
- hidden
- archived
- contained

validation_rules:
- entity_ref is required.
- duplicate active detail_code within active entity scope is prohibited.
- historical snapshots must preserve revision chain.
- sealed entity detail must not enter public publication mode.

transition_rules:
- prepared -> reviewed
- reviewed -> active
- active -> hidden
- active -> archived
- active -> contained
- contained -> hidden
- hidden -> active

operational_focus:
- profile publication
- snapshot review
- visibility incident handling
- historical snapshot inspection

failure_codes:
- ENTITY_DETAIL_OP_REF_MISSING
- ENTITY_DETAIL_OP_DUPLICATE_ACTIVE
- ENTITY_DETAIL_OP_SNAPSHOT_CHAIN_INVALID
- ENTITY_DETAIL_OP_SEALED_SCOPE_VIOLATION
